message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network Latency Measurements and Energy Consumption Under Varying Load Conditions
abstract: This dataset documents a network latency measurement experiment using a
  custom load generation tool, MoonGen, to evaluate performance under different configurations.
  The methodology involved configuring a device under test environment, executing
  a looped workload with varying packet rates and sizes, and capturing associated
  energy consumption data per run. Latency measurements were recorded during the execution
  of the load generator process, and resulting histograms were generated for analysis.
  Per-run logs and evaluation outputs are included to support reproducibility and
  detailed investigation.
